# Optional. A GitHub token used only at build time to fetch repo highlights and
# activity via the authenticated API (authenticated GraphQL = 5,000 points/hr and
# a single request for all repos; unauthenticated REST is limited to 60 req/hr
# per IP). The site still builds without it — it falls back to the unauthenticated
# API and, if GitHub is unreachable, to empty sections.
#
# A fine-grained or classic token with public read access is sufficient; no scopes
# beyond reading public data are required. In CI this is supplied automatically as
# secrets.GITHUB_TOKEN (see .github/workflows/deploy.yml).
GITHUB_TOKEN=
